@startuml
' @id(SEQ-INIT-SCAFFOLD)
' @ref(USE-INIT-FORCE)
' @ref(USE-INIT-MIGRATE)
' @ref(USE-INIT-RALPH)
' @desc(SEQ-INIT-SCAFFOLD, "Implemented flow of one `mdd init [--force]`. Commands::Init { force } (crates/mdd-cli/src/main.rs) picks the conflict handler — an always-Overwrite closure when force, else prompt_init_conflict — and calls Project::init_with_conflict_handler (crates/mdd-core/src/lib.rs). The engine creates missing directories (including .mdd/ralph); writes each REGENERABLE file via write_text_if_missing(handler) (create when missing, else overwrite-or-skip per the handler) — including the mdd-ralph SKILL.md under .claude/.codex and .mdd/ralph/PROMPT.md; refreshes the CLAUDE.md/AGENTS.md managed blocks and upserts the SessionStart hook (CMP-INIT-HOOK); writes the SeededOnce file .mdd/ralph/PLAN.md via write_text_create_if_missing (create from template when missing, else skip — no handler); and writes each of the three STATE files via write_yaml_create_or_migrate (create from default when missing, forward-migrate when on-disk version is older, else skip). It returns InitReport { created, overwritten, migrated, skipped } which the CLI prints line by line. Neither the SeededOnce nor the state branch receives the handler, so --force never overwrites PLAN.md or config/trace/approvals.")
' Current-side sequence for cycle 0018 (force + migrate) and cycle 0022
' (the SeededOnce PLAN.md branch): one init invocation, three file classes
' — regenerable (handler-driven), seeded-once and accumulating state (both
' handler-independent).
title mdd init [--force] — regenerable overwrite vs state migration (current)

actor "Developer / Agent" as Dev
participant "mdd init [--force]\n(Commands::Init)" as Cli
participant "Project::init_with_\nconflict_handler" as Engine
participant "write_text_if_missing\n(regenerable)" as Text
participant "write_text_create_\nif_missing (seeded-once)" as Seed
participant "write_yaml_create_\nor_migrate (state)" as Yaml

Dev -> Cli : mdd init [--force]
alt force flag set
  Cli -> Cli : handler = always Overwrite
else no flag (default)
  Cli -> Cli : handler = prompt_init_conflict ([o/S])
end
Cli -> Engine : init_with_conflict_handler(handler)
Engine -> Engine : create missing directories

group regenerable files (docs, skills, blocks, hook)
  Engine -> Text : write_text_if_missing(handler)
  alt missing
    Text --> Engine : create
  else exists + handler=Overwrite
    Text --> Engine : overwrite
  else exists + handler=Skip
    Text --> Engine : skip
  end
end

group seeded-once file (.mdd/ralph/PLAN.md) — handler NOT consulted
  Engine -> Seed : write_text_create_if_missing(PLAN.md)
  alt missing
    Seed --> Engine : create from template
  else exists
    Seed --> Engine : skip (never overwritten, even by --force)
  end
end

group state files (config / trace / approvals) — handler NOT consulted
  Engine -> Yaml : create_or_migrate::<T>()
  alt missing
    Yaml --> Engine : create from default
  else on_disk.version < current
    Yaml --> Engine : migrate (parse->bump version->write)
  else on_disk.version >= current
    Yaml --> Engine : skip (idempotent / never downgrade)
  end
end

Engine --> Cli : InitReport { created, overwritten, migrated, skipped }
Cli --> Dev : print summary lines
@enduml
